Add bootstrap_identity() invocation in startup flow (before FirstBootAnnouncer) so first boots mint and persist identity automatically..\\n./sdp/logs/Lead_T-021_20260416T054258Z_1776368478.log:{\\\"type\\\":\\\"message\\\",\\\"timestamp\\\":\\\"2026-04-16T19:41:21.567Z\\\",\\\"role\\\":\\\"user\\\",\\\"content\\\":\\\"# Task T-021@20260416T054258Z: Add post-tonal, spectral, and microtonal material strategies.\\\\n\\\\n## Acceptance Criteria\\\\n\\\\n- composer can request pitch-class sets, spectral partial-derived harmony, just-intonation ratios, and 24-TET/ratio pitch events when phase/style permits<br/>- SenseWeave spectral analysis can seed harmonic material<br/>- tests verify generated material remains bounded and tagged as post-tonal/spectral/microtonal\\\\n\\\\n**Tier:** T2 — Standard (New feature / moderate refactoring)\\\\n\\\\n## Instructions\\\\n\\\\nRead the project's ADP documentation and understand existing patterns before making changes.\\\\n\\\\n**ADP Phases:** Explore → Specify → Test → Implement → Verify → Document\\\\n\\\\n### Phase 0: Explore\\\\n- Read all files in the affected area of the codebase.\\\\n- Identify existing patterns, naming conventions, and architectural decisions.\\\\n- Review related tests to understand expected behavior.\\\\n- Update progress.md with exploration findings.\\\\n\\\\n### Phase 1: Specify\\\\n- Write a specification to `specs/t-021@20260416t054258z-spec.md`.\\\\n- Include: problem statement, technical approach, edge cases, acceptance criteria.\\\\n- Each acceptance criterion must have a VERIFY command.\\\\n\\\\n### Phase 2: Test Development\\\\n- Write tests BEFORE implementation, derived from the specification.\\\\n- Tests must FAIL before implementation (Red phase).\\\\n- After this phase, test files are LOCKED — do not modify assertions.\\\\n\\\\n### Phase 3: Implement\\\\n- Implement the minimum code needed to pass all tests.\\\\n- One sub-task at a time, commit each logical unit.\\\\n- Type hints on all function signatures.\\\\n- Follow existing patterns.\\\\n\\\\n### Phase 4: Verify & Document\\\\n- Run full test suite and quality checks.\\\\n- Update CHANGELOG.md, progress.md.\\\\n\\\\n## Rules\\\\n\\\\n- No questions — document assumptions in ESCALATIONS.md.\\\\n- Do not modify locked test assertions.\\\\n- Log new dependencies to ESCALATIONS.md.\\\\n- Commit per sub-task: `feat(scope): summary [T-021@20260416T054258Z]`\\\\n\\\\n## Common Pitfalls (from recurring verify feedback)\\\\n\\\\nThese are the top reasons tasks get PASS WITH NOTES instead of clean PASS.\\\\nAvoid them on the first attempt:\\\\n\\\\n- **Always include a migration** when adding or modifying database columns.\\\\n  A new model or column without a migration is a deployment gap.\\\\n- **Commit all changes** before the verify phase begins. Uncommitted work\\\\n  is flagged as blocking by the verifier.\\\\n- **Stay in scope** — only commit work under this task's ID. Do not bundle\\\\n  changes from adjacent subtasks or refactor unrelated code.\\\\n- **Add indexes on new FK columns** in `__table_args__` when adding\\\\n  foreign key relationships.\\\\n- **Keep CHANGELOG entries consistent** with actual behavior. Do not copy\\\\n  descriptions from other tasks or specs without verifying they match\\\\n  the implemented code.\\\\n\\\\n## Validation\\\\n\\\\nRun before final commit:\\\\n```bash\\\\npip install -e '.[dev]' && pytest tests/ -x && ruff check src/ tests/ && mypy src/\\\\n```\\\\n\\\\nAll must pass.\\\\n\\\\n## Candidate Hardening (Auto-Generated)\\\\n\\\\nUse the recurring failure patterns below as mandatory hardening checks:\\\\n- Address this recurring failure mode explicitly: Runtime does not invoke bootstrap_identity on startup, so the identity file is never guaranteed to be created automatically at first run. Severity: blocking.\\\\n- Address this recurring failure mode explicitly: Add bootstrap_identity() invocation in startup flow (before FirstBootAnnouncer) so first boots mint and persist identity automatically..\\\\n- Address this recurring failure mode explicitly: Ensure this path is used on both standalone and federated modes..\\\\n- Enforce behavioral regression tests before completion: Add an integration test that exercises startup and verifies identity persistence between boots..\\\\n- Enforce behavioral regression tests before completion: Re-run pip install -e '.[dev]' && pytest tests/ -x after wiring the startup path..\\\\n\\\"}\\n./sdp/logs/Lead_T-021_20260416T054258Z_1776368478.log:{\\\"type\\\":\\\"tool_result\\\",\\\"timestamp\\\":\\\"2026-04-16T19:41:53.976Z\\\",\\\"tool_id\\\":\\\"run_shell_command_1776368513886_0\\\",\\\"status\\\":\\\"success\\\",\\\"output\\\":\\\"diff --git a/my-claw/tools/audio_analysis.py b/my-claw/tools/audio_analysis.py\\\\nindex 5bc9767..db6a731 100644\\\\n--- a/my-claw/tools/audio_analysis.py\\\\n+++ b/my-claw/tools/audio_analysis.py\\\\n@@ -349,3 +349,81 @@ def pitch_to_nearest_key(frequency_hz: float) -> tuple[str, list[str]]:\\\\n     note_idx = round(midi) % 12\\\\n     root = _NOTE_NAMES[note_idx]\\\\n     return root, _KEY_SCALES[root]\\\\n+\\\\n+\\\\n+def extract_spectral_peaks(\\\\n+    samples: list[int] | list[float],\\\\n+    sample_rate: int,\\\\n+    *,\\\\n+    max_peaks: int = 4,\\\\n+    min_freq: float = 20.0,\\\\n+    max_freq: float = 12000.0,\\\\n+) -> list[float]:\\\\n+    \\\\\\\"\\\\\\\"\\\\\\\"Extract prominent spectral peaks using a pure Python radix-2 FFT approach.\\\\\\\"\\\\\\\"\\\\\\\"\\\\n+    if not samples:\\\\n+        return []\\\\n+    \\\\n+    n = 1024\\\\n+    if len(samples) > n:\\\\n+        start = (len(samples) - n) // 2\\\\n+        window = samples[start:start + n]\\\\n+    else:\\\\n+        window = list(samples)\\\\n+        n = len(window)\\\\n+    \\\\n+    p = 1\\\\n+    while p < n: p *= 2\\\\n+    if p != n:\\\\n+        window.extend([0.0] * (p - n))\\\\n+        n = p\\\\n+\\\\n+    def reverse_bits(val: int, width: int) -> int:\\\\n+        res = 0\\\\n+        for _ in range(width):\\\\n+            res = (res << 1) | (val & 1)\\\\n+            val >>= 1\\\\n+        return res\\\\n+        \\\\n+    width = n.bit_length() - 1\\\\n+    x_real = [float(s) for s in window]\\\\n+    x_imag = [0.0] * n\\\\n+    \\\\n+    # Bit-reversal permutation\\\\n+    for i in range(n):\\\\n+        rev = reverse_bits(i, width)\\\\n+        if i < rev:\\\\n+            x_real[i], x_real[rev] = x_real[rev], x_real[i]\\\\n+        \\\\n+    # Cooley-Tukey Radix-2\\\\n+    step = 1\\\\n+    while step < n:\\\\n+        half_step = step\\\\n+        step <<= 1\\\\n+        theta_step = -2.0 * math.pi / step\\\\n+        for i in range(half_step):\\\\n+            theta = i * theta_step\\\\n+            wr = math.cos(theta)\\\\n+            wi = math.sin(theta)\\\\n+            for j in range(i, n, step):\\\\n+                k = j + half_step\\\\n+                tr = wr * x_real[k] - wi * x_imag[k]\\\\n+                ti = wr * x_imag[k] + wi * x_real[k]\\\\n+                x_real[k] = x_real[j] - tr\\\\n+                x_imag[k] = x_imag[j] - ti\\\\n+                x_real[j] += tr\\\\n+                x_imag[j] += ti\\\\n+\\\\n+    magnitudes = []\\\\n+    for i in range(n // 2):\\\\n+        mag = math.sqrt(x_real[i]**2 + x_imag[i]**2)\\\\n+        freq = i * sample_rate / n\\\\n+        if min_freq <= freq <= max_freq:\\\\n+            magnitudes.append((freq, mag))\\\\n+            \\\\n+    peaks = []\\\\n+    for i in range(1, len(magnitudes) - 1):\\\\n+        if magnitudes[i][1] > magnitudes[i-1][1] and magnitudes[i][1] > magnitudes[i+1][1]:\\\\n+            peaks.append(magnitudes[i])\\\\n+            \\\\n+    peaks.sort(key=lambda x: x[1], reverse=True)\\\\n+    return [p[0] for p in peaks[:max_peaks]]\\\\ndiff --git a/my-claw/tools/cypherclaw_daemon.py b/my-claw/tools/cypherclaw_daemon.py\\\\nindex d5cd67c..f2cc862 100644\\\\n--- a/my-claw/tools/cypherclaw_daemon.py\\\\n+++ b/my-claw/tools/cypherclaw_daemon.py\\