./sdp/logs/Lead_T-013_20260425T183959Za_1777156511.log:8535:The doc and regression test are green. I’m in the bookkeeping pass now: adding the task-scoped changelog/progress entries and then I’ll run the repo’s required validation command so this closes out cleanly instead of as a docs-only partial.
./sdp/logs/Lead_T-013_20260425T183959Za_1777156511.log:8547:- Added audio-rendered novelty verification for SenseWeave fixtures: `render.audio_novelty` now writes deterministic 5-minute proxy WAVs, extracts librosa mel-feature self-similarity matrices plus Foote novelty curves, aligns symbolic CCH-034 novelty peak times to audio peaks within 500 ms, and fails flattened synthesis even when symbolic metrics remain healthy.
./sdp/logs/Lead_T-013_20260425T183959Za_1777156511.log:8550:- Added operator diagnostics for production-course decisions: `operator_diagnostics.py` now extracts production-course chapter values (phase, scale/mode, harmonic function, groove, production strategy, mix role, spatial profile) from tracker runtime `scene_metadata` with fallback to score-tree sections; Theramini relation combines counterpoint relation with live Theramini playing state; critique notes derive threshold violations from ear-engine metrics; all three fields degrade gracefully to "unavailable" when authority files are absent or corrupt; `/status` display renders the new fields in the SenseWeave section.
./sdp/logs/Lead_T-013_20260425T183959Za_1777156511.log:8551:- Added executable production-course curriculum exercises: `ExerciseSpec` now carries a runnable `template` and explicit `expected_features` while preserving the legacy `expected` alias; generated exercise specs include both metadata forms; and the EMSD curriculum now has verifier-backed exercises for intervals/scales, chord voicings, progressions, rhythm/groove, counterpoint, synthesis architecture, mix/master, SenseWeave mapping, Theramini ensemble, genre strategy, and full-arc production.
./sdp/logs/Lead_T-013_20260425T183959Za_1777156511.log:8552:- Added course-driven self-critique and revision targets: `self_critique.py` now maps production-course chapter concepts (mode_scale, harmonic_function, meter_groove, counterpoint_relation, synthesis_architecture, mix_role, spatial_intent, genre_strategy, transition_type, phase_profile) to concrete ear-engine metric thresholds via `COURSE_METRIC_MAP`; `thresholds_for_course()` merges per-section course metadata into quality thresholds (stricter wins); `critique_score_with_course()` returns a `CourseCritiqueReport` with `CourseFailure` attribution naming the specific course concept behind each metric violation; `revision_targets_from_failures()` maps failures to `RevisionTargets` specifying which musical dimensions (form, harmony, rhythm, register, mix, strategy) are open for bounded revision without changing piece identity; `revise_score()` accepts an optional `course` kwarg; `tracker_compiler.py` and `duet_composer.py` fallback paths now pass section production_course to `revise_score`.
./sdp/logs/Lead_T-013_20260425T183959Za_1777156511.log:8554:- Added dissonance/resolution metadata checks to counterpoint rules using music_theory.py interval consonance data: new `DissonanceAnnotation` and `DissonanceReport` dataclasses carry full `Interval` objects from the music theory library; `analyze_dissonance()` annotates each vertical interval in a voice-pair sequence with consonance classification and stepwise resolution status; `verify_resolution_sequence()` validates that all sharp dissonances resolve properly; `resolution_completeness_score()` returns a 0.0-1.0 ratio; and `weighted_voice_leading_smoothness()` penalizes unresolved dissonances in the smoothness metric.
./sdp/logs/Lead_T-013_20260425T183959Za_1777156511.log:8557:- Added artistic identity portfolio reporting and surface snapshots: new `portfolio_report.py` module provides `derive_portfolio_report()` for comprehensive identity summaries from repertoire metrics, preferred forms/modes, motif counts, practice block coverage with EMSD course codes, growth-state keys, and ear quality averages; and `derive_surface_snapshot()` for face/operator display data (current song title, section caption, practice block, artistic-intent line). Graceful degradation handles empty repertoire, missing fields, corrupt score trees, and absent growth state without hallucinating data.
./sdp/logs/Lead_T-013_20260425T183959Za_1777156511.log:8560:- Added pre-performance self-critique and bounded revision passes: new `self_critique.py` module provides `preview_score()` for offline metric analysis, `critique_score()` for threshold-based quality gating, and `revise_score()` for one bounded rewrite attempt that preserves piece identity (key, mood, tempo) while improving at least one failed metric.
./sdp/logs/Lead_T-013_20260425T183959Za_1777156511.log:8563:- Rebalanced the first live score-tree pass for audibility: fresh post-restart commissions now avoid jumping straight to a maximal sparse suite unless the cadence is already wind-down/sleep-oriented, and `music_tracker_runtime.py` now emits stronger safe amplitudes for primary melody/bass/rhythm lanes so a healthy running piece is easier to hear and meter.
./sdp/logs/Lead_T-013_20260425T183959Za_1777156511.log:8564:- Fixed the long-section tracker compile bug that was turning songs into isolated sustained tones: `tracker_compiler.py` now converts large section budgets into repeat counts plus modest note-length scaling, and `music_tracker.py` quantizes those repeats into real repeated phrase cycles instead of stretching a handful of notes across the whole scene.
./sdp/logs/Lead_T-013_20260425T183959Za_1777156511.log:8565:- Finished the next score-tree composition pass: `tracker_compiler.py` now derives and enriches a fresh score per section, applies section-function and motif-aware phrase transforms before tracker quantization, and `music_tracker.py` now varies repeated cycles inside long sections, so longer pieces can develop through distinct section writing instead of only looping one shared phrase body.
./sdp/logs/Lead_T-013_20260425T183959Za_1777156511.log:8566:- Added internal phrase-family development inside longer sections: `Phrase` now carries metadata, `tracker_compiler.py` expands section bodies into recursive families like `A`, `A_prime`, and `B`, and `music_tracker.py` annotates emitted steps with `internal_phrase_family` so development sections can be tested and diagnosed as more than literal loops.
./sdp/logs/Lead_T-013_20260425T183959Za_1777156511.log:8568:- Added authored section transitions: `tracker_compiler.py` now tags each non-final scene with the next scene/function/root target, and `music_tracker.py` marks and retunes final-cycle tail steps as transition preparation so long sections aim into the following section instead of simply looping until a hard boundary.
./sdp/logs/Lead_T-013_20260425T183959Za_1777156511.log:8569:- Added staged lane windows inside repeated tracker scenes: `music_tracker.py` now assigns per-role `entry_cycle` / `exit_cycle` metadata and delays counter/color support in long development-style sections, so sections can thicken internally instead of launching every lane at row 0.
./sdp/logs/Lead_T-013_20260425T183959Za_1777156511.log:8571:- Added section-level motif development and local harmonic progressions: `tracker_compiler.py` now labels each section as statement, sequence/fragment, contrast inversion, recall answer, liquidation, or residue, reshapes phrase material accordingly, and applies section-local progressions that are exposed on tracker scenes and steps for bass/progression verification.
./sdp/logs/Lead_T-013_20260425T183959Za_1777156511.log:8573:- Fixed recalled motif rhythm metadata so later sections that borrow earlier material inherit the current scene's rhythm/progression profile instead of leaking the source scene's old `rhythm_development`.
./sdp/logs/Lead_T-013_20260425T183959Za_1777156511.log:8574:- Added arrangement automation curves to tracker playback: `music_tracker.py` now derives `arrangement_curve` from section rhythm, writes row-point automation for `density`, `master_amp`, and `reverb_send`, shapes note velocity across each lane's active window, and `music_tracker_runtime.py` / `duet_composer.py` now expose and apply interpolated automation to the live master bus during the section. Low density also thins optional color/counter runtime events while preserving melody and bass continuity.
./sdp/logs/Lead_T-013_20260425T183959Za_1777156511.log:8576:- Rebalanced the live song mix after the repeat-cycle fix: `music_tracker_runtime.py` now gives texture lanes a stronger floor while slightly easing bass dominance, and `emsd_performance.py` now uses a gentler amp-scaling curve so normal `away_practice` songs no longer pin bass and melody at the top of the EMSD gain range.
